Mmino - iOS band app

Thank you for purchasing Mmino - iOS band app. If you have any questions that are beyond the scope of this help file, please feel free to email via our user page contact form. Thanks so much!

  • created: 05/30/2016
  • latest update: 05/31/2016
  • by: RockStar_Media

App Quick Start

  • You should have MAC OSX
  • With Xcode installed (latest version)
  • And a server or host where you can upload the admin panel and your media files

App Features

  • Push Notifications
  • Social Sharing
  • Video on Demand
  • Events Calendar
  • Live Video Streaming
  • Live Audio Streaming
  • Admin Panel

AI Files

You are provided with .ai files, open them with illustrator to modify them.



	

	

	

	

	





	
HTML Files and Structure



	You are provided with a www folder in MainFiles which has well documented html, css and js files. Open your project in xcode and change Bundle Identifier. Expand Staging then www folder then templates. Thats where all HTML files located.


<div ng-controller="ambitiouzEntertainmentCtrl">
  <ion-view class=" " id="literBg" title="Ambitiouz Entertainment">
      <ion-content padding="false" class=" manual-remove-top-padding has-header">
      <img src="img/home/home.png" width="100%" height="auto">
          <div class="button-bar" style="padding-bottom: 1em; position: fixed; top:0">
              <a class=" button button-positive  button-clear" ng-click="openSongs()"></a>

          </div>





	
Admin Panel



	Unzip your mmino.zip, and open the adminpanel folder you will see install.sql file. Create a MySQL database and import the install.sql file.

	

	Browse for db_conx.php in mmino/adminpanel/includes/db_conx.php. Open it and input your

	"SERVER_NAME", "USERNAME","PASSWORD" and "DATABASE_NAME".

	

	NB: Create a login page for your admin panel, that way, only you will have access to it.





	Once your done, your Admin Panel should look like this...





	





	
JavaScript Files



	Expand your 'js' folder and open services.js.


angular.module('app.services', [])

.factory('consUrl', function() {
    return "http://YOURDOMAIN/mmnino/adminpanel/includes/encode/index.php/?get=";
})

.factory('StreamService', function($http, $stateParams, consUrl) {
        "use strict";
        var get_url = consUrl;
        return {
            getStream: function(){
                var stream = [];
                return $http.get(get_url+"stream").then(function(response){
                    stream = response;
                    return stream;
                });
            }
    };
})

Push Notifications



	In order to use Push Notifications you need to create an account in OneSignal.com 



	In XCODE, expand Staging/www/js/ and open 'app.js' then change 'OneSignal_AppId'


window.plugins.OneSignal.init("OneSignal_AppId",
                                 {googleProjectNumber: ""},
                                 notificationOpenedCallback);

  •
